President Obama will award former Army Sergeant Kyle J. White the Medal of Honor for his courageous actions during combat operations in Afghanistan in 2007. Sergeant White, who served as a Platoon Radio Telephone Operator, will be the seventh living recipient to receive the Medal of Honor for actions in Iraq or Afghanistan. He currently works as an Investment Analyst in Charlotte, NC. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who demonstrate gallantry above and beyond the call of duty, involving great personal bravery or self-sacrifice.